The FBI is accepting tips and digital media depicting rioting and violence in the U.S. Capitol Building and surrounding area in Washington, DC, on January 6, 2021. If you have witnessed unlawful violent actions, we urge you to submit any information, photos, or videos that could be relevant at fbi.gov/USCapitol. Please use this form to submit any images, videos, or other

long_object.body: You know what...I RT’d this without actually looking at it myself. Then I read an article about some of the folks they’ve already arrested. Listen to me. They walk among us. Stop. LOOK. Yes! They should’ve been arrested on the spot. But it’s not too late to hold them accountable!

actor.summary: Welcome to the official Twitter page of the FBI. Do not report tips here. Submit tips on federal crime or terrorism at https://t.co/bvLnLbg98y. For emergencies, dial 911.

long_object.body: The #FBI is still seeking information to help identify individuals who actively instigated violence on January 6 in Washington, D.C. Visit https://t.co/h36NpdxbEh to see images from current cases, and if you see someone you recognize, submit a tip at https://t.co/buMd8vYXzH. https://t.co/cGgWNeywIc

urls.expanded_url_title: Capitol Violence | Federal Bureau of Investigation
urls.expanded_url_description: The FBI is seeking to identify individuals involved in the violent activities that occurred at the U.S. Capitol and surrounding areas on January 6, 2021. View posters and related information here. If you have any information to provide, visit fbi.gov/USCapitol or call 1-800-CALL-FBI.

urls.expanded_url_title: FBI — FBI Seeking Information Related to Violent Activity at the U.S Capitol Building
urls.expanded_url_description: The FBI is seeking information that will assist in identifying individuals who are actively instigating violence in Washington, DC. The FBI is accepting tips and digital media depicting rioting and violence in the U.S. Capitol Building and surrounding area in Washington, DC, on January 6, 2021. If you have witnessed unlawful violent actions, we urge you to submit any information, photos, or videos that could be relevant at fbi.gov/USCapitol. Please use this form to submit any images, videos, or other
